SIMPLE: scaled
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scaled
<hw>Scaled</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Covered
with scales, or scalelike structures; -- said of a fish, a reptile, a
moth, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Without scales, or with the scales removed; <as>as,
<ex>scaled</ex> herring</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having feathers which in form,
color, or arrangement somewhat resemble scales; <as>as, the
<ex>scaled</ex> dove</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Scaled dove</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any
American dove of the genus <gen>Scardafella</gen>. Its colored feather
tips resemble scales.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scaleless</ent>⟦br⟧
